  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before I narrate about our second arrival to Stanislau, I want to mention I forgot to give the date when my father died in 1943.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was March 25th on the [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Julian ?] calendar, and it was 18 days [HEBREW] on the Hebrew calendar.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We are now in 1943.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were shipped out from Hungary as a labor unit to the Eastern front.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Our first stop is the city of Stanislau.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I have to mention that [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] we all knew that shipping out to the Eastern front was a very, very dangerous journey.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When we were in [INAUDIBLE] before-- before we were shipped out, there came a representative of a church-- I don't remember of what church-- and they proposed to whoever would convert to Christianity would be taken out of this camp, labor camp, and put in a special camp with no yellow bands.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I have to say-- out of the 200 and [? twenty-some ?] boys that were in this group, only one boy acquiesced to that proposition, and he was taken out.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because we knew that once we were shipped out to the Eastern front, our whole existence depended entirely on the commander of our-- of our company.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now, in spite of that great fear, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we-- we relied on our destiny.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Whatever will be will be.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we arrived to the city of Stanislau.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We were put in empty houses that were Jewish houses before.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] That was the first couple of days that we were there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] We all knew that the city of Stanislau had a very large Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And here we saw, when he came in there, we saw this terrible destruction.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
